abstract: >
  An open-source desktop GUI wrapping a multi-agent pipeline for molecular
  docking using AutoDock Vina. Accepts a compound name (PubChem) and one or
  more receptor PDB IDs (RCSB), then runs the full end-to-end workflow:
  ligand preparation with RDKit and Meeko, receptor cleanup, docking with
  AutoDock Vina, and report generation. Agent orchestration uses a local
  large language model via Ollama so the tool runs fully offline after
  one-time setup. Designed as a teaching aid for MBBS and PG pharmacology
  students learning structure-based drug design concepts.
